quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  25,44,"Or do you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>assume that most of them hear or reason? They are but like livestock; rather, they are even further astray from the way."
  25,45,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not seen how your Lord extended the shade? And had He willed, He could have made it still. Then We made the sun a guide to it."
  25,46,"Then We drew it to Us easily."
  25,47,"And it is He Who made the night for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>as a garment and sleep for repose, and made the day a<i class=""s"">(time of) </i>resurrection."
  25,48,"And it is He Who sent the <span class="h">winds{1}</span>as <span class="h">heralds of glad tidings{2}</span>ahead of His mercy. And We{3}sent down from the sky pure water",footnotes:1:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Kathir read it as: “wind”.</span>],footnotes:2:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Ibn Amer, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “…as revivers ahead of His mercy”. All except for Asem, Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Ibn Amer, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “… as a revival ahead of His mercy”.</span>],footnotes:3:[A grammatical shift from 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person to 1<sup><small>st</small></sup> person.]
  25,49,"to revive a lifeless land thereby, and to provide drink for a multitude of animals and humans We have created."
  25,50,"And most surely We have circulated it among them, that they may <span class="h">constantly remember{1}</span>, yet most of mankind refused anything but constant denial.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…that they may remember,”</span>
  25,51,"And had We willed, We could have sent to every town a warner."
  25,52,"So do not obey<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>the deniers, but strive against them with it{1}a supreme striving.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an.
  25,53,"And it is He Who merged the two seas, this one fresh and sweet and this one salty and bitter, and He made between them a barrier and an insurmountable separator."
  25,54,"And it is He Who created of water a human being, then made him related by lineage and marriage. And your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord has always been All-Able."
  25,55,"Yet they worship, apart from Allah, what neither benefits them nor harms them. And the denier has always been a backup against his Lord."
